          "prompt_html": "<h1>MULTIPLE CHOICE 67</h1><p><strong>Questions 21 - 26</strong></p><p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A, B, or C</strong>.</p><p>21 The main focus of the presentation about the book must be ...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... its historical details.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... the readers' reactions to it.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... biographies of the main characters.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>22 When was Sunrise Lake first published in book form?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    December 1960</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    August 1961</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    October 1961</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>23 How many other books had the author written in this narrative style before Sunrise Lake?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    One</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Two</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Ten</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>24 What do Rachel and Owen agree on about the character of Matthew?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    They both wanted him to be successful.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    They both felt pity for him from the beginning.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    They both think he is a sympathetic and highly intelligent character.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>25 Rachel and Owen both describe Sally Baxter's character as...</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    Sinister</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    Vengeful</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    Strange</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table><p>26 Regarding the character Lucy, Owen believes that ...?</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>A</strong>    ... Matthew's feelings for Lucy are reciprocated.</th><th></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>B</strong>    ... Matthew wanted to be as rich and cultured as Lucy.</td><td></td></tr><tr><td><strong>C</strong>    ... Lucy wants to hurt Matthew as Sally Baxter wishes.</td><td></td></tr></tbody></table>",
